      <item>
        <title>Error running npx</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[luisherranz]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>It seems like it is a problem of <code>npx</code> when the user folder contains an space (<code>Saad Faris</code>)</p>
<aside class="onebox githubissue">
  <header class="source">
      <a href="https://github.com/zkat/npx/issues/100" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">github.com/zkat/npx</a>
  </header>
  <article class="onebox-body">
    <a href="https://github.com/Meeeeow" rel="nofollow noopener">
<img src="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/original/1X/8bed6703989116fb88f26f6bb2bc09f6876267be.jpeg" class="thumbnail onebox-avatar" width="96" height="96">
</a>

<h4><a href="https://github.com/zkat/npx/issues/100" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Issue: Error: EPERM: operation not permitted, mkdir 'C:\Users\Foo'</a></h4>

<div class="date" style="margin-top:10px;">
	<div class="user" style="margin-top:10px;">
	opened by <a href="https://github.com/Meeeeow" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Meeeeow</a>
	on <a href="https://github.com/zkat/npx/issues/100" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">2017-07-21</a>
	</div>
	<div class="user">
	</div>
</div>

<pre class="content" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Environment: Windows 10
npx Version: 9.4.1
See also: #84
Reason:
My user home directory contain whitespace, like foo bar</pre>

<div class="labels">
 	<span style="display:inline-block;margin-top:2px;background-color: #B8B8B8;padding: 2px;border-radius: 4px;color: #fff;margin-left: 3px;">bug</span>
 	<span style="display:inline-block;margin-top:2px;background-color: #B8B8B8;padding: 2px;border-radius: 4px;color: #fff;margin-left: 3px;">help wanted</span>
 	<span style="display:inline-block;margin-top:2px;background-color: #B8B8B8;padding: 2px;border-radius: 4px;color: #fff;margin-left: 3px;">windows</span>
</div>

  </article>
  <div class="onebox-metadata">
    
    
  </div>
  <div style="clear: both"></div>
</aside>

<p>It’s crazy that they haven’t solved it yet.</p>
<p>You need to move the npm cache to a folder without spaces.</p>
<p>First, open <code>cmd</code> as Administrator.</p>
<ul>
<li>Search for <code>cmd</code>
</li>
<li>Right click</li>
<li>Choose “Run as Administraror”</li>
<li>Enter your password</li>
</ul>
<p></p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/original/1X/fa5ea452484902b14b6adf030cd88dd3ced102aa.png" data-download-href="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/fa5ea452484902b14b6adf030cd88dd3ced102aa" title="Screen Shot 2019-09-01 at 16.34.10.png"><img src="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/fa5ea452484902b14b6adf030cd88dd3ced102aa_2_295x500.png" alt="10" data-base62-sha1="zIS8ugz3jON6eIWlLpXuAiK1Qds" width="295" height="500" srcset="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/fa5ea452484902b14b6adf030cd88dd3ced102aa_2_295x500.png, https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/fa5ea452484902b14b6adf030cd88dd3ced102aa_2_442x750.png 1.5x, https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/fa5ea452484902b14b6adf030cd88dd3ced102aa_2_590x1000.png 2x" data-small-upload="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/fa5ea452484902b14b6adf030cd88dd3ced102aa_2_10x10.png"></a></div><p></p>
<p>Then enter these commands in the console:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-bash">&gt; mklink /J "C:\Users\saad-faris" "C:\Users\Saad Faris"
&gt; npm config set cache C:\Users\saad-faris\AppData\Roaming\npm-cache
&gt; npm config set prefix C:\Users\saad-faris\AppData\Roaming\npm
&gt; npm cache clean --force
</code></pre>
<p></p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/original/1X/4ce4a5d9599ed0aa36caa0a5344244be720e6952.png" data-download-href="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/4ce4a5d9599ed0aa36caa0a5344244be720e6952" title="Screen Shot 2019-09-01 at 16.38.30.png"><img src="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/4ce4a5d9599ed0aa36caa0a5344244be720e6952_2_690x374.png" alt="30" data-base62-sha1="aYea8wGIl0akjkAgYaHOktu3ZtM" width="690" height="374" srcset="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/4ce4a5d9599ed0aa36caa0a5344244be720e6952_2_690x374.png, https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/4ce4a5d9599ed0aa36caa0a5344244be720e6952_2_1035x561.png 1.5x, https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/4ce4a5d9599ed0aa36caa0a5344244be720e6952_2_1380x748.png 2x" data-small-upload="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/1X/4ce4a5d9599ed0aa36caa0a5344244be720e6952_2_10x10.png"></a></div><p></p>
<p>Let me know if that solves all the problems you’re facing.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/error-running-npx/512/8">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
